The paper discusses the use of bibliometric analysis for evaluation and international comparison of performance levels in social sciences and humanities. The paper also emphasizes the importance of combining quantitative publication counts with qualitative information from peer assessment or validation to identify categories that represent research quality as perceived by peers. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
